T1  - A Goal-Energy-Effort Requirement Model of Work Motivation
AU  - Wofford, J. C.
Y1  - 1979/04/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1979.4289018
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1979.4289018
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 193
EP  - 201
VL  - 4
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A model of work motivation is presented that postulates the following five variables as determinants of the force to perform: (a) Task Goal Level, (b) Task Goal Specificity, (c) Task Goal Commitment, (d) Energy Potential, and (e) Perceived Effort Required. Propositions for the model are presented, relevant literature is reviewed, and concepts for the model are operationalized.
AB  - A model of work motivation is presented that postulates the following five variables as determinants of the force to perform: (a) Task Goal Level, (b) Task Goal Specificity, (c) Task Goal Commitment, (d) Energy Potential, and (e) Perceived Effort Required. Propositions for the model are presented, relevant literature is reviewed, and concepts for the model are operationalized.
