N2  - A framework is presented to describe the behavior of decision makers as they recognize situations that merit action. The framework suggests how decision makers compare norms with perceptions to select deferral, evaluation, and planning responses. This framework is linked to schematics of evaluation and planning processes to illustrate how ?managerial diagnosis? determines the effectiveness of these forms of inquiry.
