TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Critique of the Vroom-Yetton Contingency Model Of Leadership Behavior
AU  - Field, R. H. George
Y1  - 1979/04/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1979.4289023
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1979.4289023
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 249
EP  - 257
VL  - 4
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The Vroom-Yetton contingency model of leadership behavior is described and critiqued. While there is some evidence for the validity of the model, the use of concurrent validation with self-report data seriously questions this validity. The model is of limited utility because it deals with only one aspect of leader behavior and is not as parsimonious as alternative models.
AB  - The Vroom-Yetton contingency model of leadership behavior is described and critiqued. While there is some evidence for the validity of the model, the use of concurrent validation with self-report data seriously questions this validity. The model is of limited utility because it deals with only one aspect of leader behavior and is not as parsimonious as alternative models.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1979.4289023
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1979.4289023
